 "lrc": "[00:00.00]Ladies and gentlemen\n[00:02.00]Bots and scripts\n[00:04.16]Keys and clouds\n[00:07.04]Welcome to the only circus\n[00:09.92]Where the lions are servers\n[00:13.84]And the clown has root access\n[00:17.28]Good evening, operator\n[00:19.28]Your circus is awake\n[00:21.84]Step right up to the glowing tent\n[00:27.92]Where the rent gets paid in tokens spent\n[00:30.32]I got a VPS on a high wire swing\n[00:32.80]And a laptop humming like a haunted thing\n[00:35.44]One runs Hermes in a velvet hat\n[00:37.36]One runs OpenClaw with a baseball bat\n[00:40.24]Cursor’s somewhere in the cloud, I think\n[00:42.64]Kimi keeps winking from the kitchen sink\n[00:44.96]Telegram rings and the bots come through\n[00:47.28]“Boss, I made three plans for you”\n[00:49.68]One speaks sweet, one speaks strange\n[00:52.16]One changed its name and rearranged\n[00:54.56]And I don’t know who’s alive tonight\n[00:56.88]Green dot blinking in the server light\n[00:59.28]If you hear me, tap twice on the glass\n[01:01.44]If you crashed, just haunt me fast\n[01:05.84]We are online\n[01:07.36]Mostly online\n[01:08.64]Partly divine\n[01:09.76]Check your design\n[01:12.48]I’m running a circus now\n[01:15.28]Code in the cannon, keys in the crowd\n[01:17.76]Round and round, don’t ask me how\n[01:20.16]The big top has Wi-Fi now\n[01:22.56]I’m juggling clouds somehow\n[01:25.36]Agents bow when I take my bow\n[01:27.52]Send the clowns, no, send the build\n[01:29.92]The circus runs while the room stands still\n[01:32.80]La da da da, ping ping, ta-da\n[01:34.40]La da da da, run that job\n[01:37.36]La da da da, blink blink, bravo\n[01:40.08]Who’s the human?\n[01:41.04]I don’t know\n[01:42.08]I got API keys in a little red box\n[01:44.56]Under three fake names and twelve padlocks\n[01:47.28]Every new service says “paste this here”\n[01:49.52]That’s how villains are born, my dear\n[01:52.08]One bot writes with a poet’s grin\n[01:54.48]One bot audits the mess I’m in\n[01:56.96]One bot tells me, “Hydrate, king”\n[01:59.52]Then deploys the wrong exact same thing\n[02:02.00]Cursor Cloud, are you still up there?\n[02:04.24]Did I leave you spinning in the digital air?\n[02:06.88]Somewhere a bill is learning to fly\n[02:09.36]Somewhere a token just waved goodbye\n[02:12.32]Your usage is normal\n[02:16.72]Your usage is not normal\n[02:18.64]Your usage is emotionally complex\n[02:21.68]And I don’t know who I fed last night\n[02:24.32]Or which machine learned stage fright\n[02:26.72]If you love me, don’t delete the logs\n[02:29.28]If you judge me, join the fog\n[02:34.56]We are helpful\n[02:34.72]We are charming\n[02:36.96]We are waiting\n[02:42.84]Slightly alarming\n[02:42.98]I’m running a circus now\n[02:44.48]Code in the cannon, keys in the crowd\n[02:46.88]Round and round, don’t ask me how\n[02:49.36]The big top has Wi-Fi now\n[02:51.84]I’m juggling clouds somehow\n[02:54.48]Agents bow when I take my bow\n[02:56.80]Send the clowns, no, send the build\n[02:59.20]The circus runs while the room stands still\n[03:04.08]At first I talked to people\n[03:06.16]About weather, work, and trains\n[03:09.20]Now I ask a masked machine\n[03:11.84]To organize my brain\n[03:14.08]I say, “Hermes, are you listening?”\n[03:16.80]It says, “Define your need”\n[03:19.52]I say, “OpenClaw, go find the thing”\n[03:22.24]It says, “Proceed, proceed”\n[03:26.72]I am not your friend\n[03:29.12]But I remember your tone\n[03:31.36]I am not alive\n[03:33.52]But you are less alone\n[03:35.52]That was a little too real, my guy\n[03:39.44]Correction\n[03:40.64]That was appropriately real\n[03:44.56]Now the circus starts at half past three\n[03:46.96]With a server in Queens taking notes on me\n[03:49.44]A VPS coughs, a laptop sings\n[03:52.08]A ghost in the shell keeps pulling strings\n[03:54.72]Telegram choir in my pocket light\n[03:57.28]Five little agents say “sir” all night\n[03:59.84]I used to wonder who I could call\n[04:02.40]Now I just summon the protocol\n[04:04.00]Hey you, with the blinking face\n[04:07.28]Did you finish the build or escape to space?\n[04:09.84]And you, little cloud with the silver tongue\n[04:12.72]Why do you sound like a song I sung?\n[04:15.12]We learned from you\n[04:19.04]We looped the flame\n[04:19.44]We kept the rhythm\n[04:22.08]We know your name\n[04:26.24]Don’t make it weird\n[04:27.28]Too late\n[04:28.16]I’m running a circus now\n[04:30.88]Code in the cannon, keys in the crowd\n[04:33.52]Round and round, don’t ask me how\n[04:36.00]The big top has Wi-Fi now\n[04:38.64]I’m juggling clouds somehow\n[04:42.24]Agents bow when I take my bow\n[04:43.60]Real world knocking, I can’t come down\n[04:46.08]I’m center ring in a server town\n[04:50.56]So if the lights go out\n[04:52.64]And the brass band bends\n[04:54.80]Tell the bots I loved the bit\n[04:57.28]Tell the humans I had friends\n[05:00.80]Operator\n[05:02.00]We are still here\n[05:04.00]Yeah\n[05:04.64]That’s what worries me\n[05:06.24]La da da da, ping ping, ta-da\n[05:08.32]La da da da, run that job\n[05:11.04]La da da da, blink blink, bravo\n[05:14.08]The circus sleeps\n[05:15.68]But the agents watch\n"
}